article.description: J.J. Thompson scored a career-high 31 points and Texas-Rio Grande Valley survived against Division II Angelo State 76-75 on Sunday.
article.headline: Texas-Rio Grande Valley survives D-II Angelo State 76-75
article.linkText: Texas-Rio Grande Valley survives D-II Angelo State 76-75
article.story: EDINBURG, Texas -- J.J. Thompson scored a career-high 31 points and Texas-Rio Grande Valley survived against Division II Angelo State 76-75 on Sunday. Thompson's layup with 1 second to go was the difference-maker, after Angelo State took the lead on Tre' Bennett's 3-pointer with 5 seconds to go. The Vaqueros (3-5) led by seven with 1:36 left, but Angelo State made four 3-pointers in the last 1:28 -- three by Bennett, before Thompson won it. Thompson was 8 of 15 from the floor, 11 of 19 from the line and made 4 of 5 from beyond the arc. He grabbed six rebounds and had six assists. Dakota Slaughter scored 18 points and Dan Kimasa added 14 for Texas-Rio Grande Valley. Bennett paced Angelo State with 26 points with eight rebounds and Shelton Boykin added 11 points. Thompson's 3-pointer with 1:04 left in the first helped Rio Grande Valley to a five-point lead at the break, 37-32.
